Local HQ of Preparatory Committee for Joint Functions Formed in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 26 (KCNA) -- The South Kyongsang Provincial Headquarters of the south side's preparatory committee for joint functions of Koreans in the north and the south and overseas to implement the June 15 joint declaration was reportedly inaugurated with due ceremony in Masan, South Kyongsang Province, on May 20.
 The ceremony elected permanent representative, executive chairman and 14 advisers and 23 members of its advisory committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Read out at the ceremony were congratulatory letters sent by the preparatory committees of the north, the south and overseas sides for joint functions of Koreans in the north and the south and overseas to implement the joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The 60-year-long national division has brought unspeakable pain and misfortune to the Korean nation but our people have waged an indomitable struggle to achieve national reunification without fail, thus ushering in the June 15 era, the inaugural declaration noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The South Kyongsang Provincial Headquarters will join efforts and wisdom with all other compatriots in the efforts to achieve national reunification free from any interference of outside forces in the spirit of the joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will make all efforts to frustrate all military actions to threaten peace on the Korean Peninsula and achieve genuine peace on this land.
 We will join people of all social standings in South Kyongsang Province in the vigorous movement to make this year, which marks the 5th anniversary of the June 15 joint declaration and the 60th anniversary of the national liberation, a year of bringing about a turning phase for the independent reunification and hand down a reunified country to posterity.

Reception Given on "Day of Africa" 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 26 (KCNA) -- Diplomatic envoys of Egypt, Libya and Nigeria hosted a reception at the Taedonggang Club for the Diplomatic Corps on May 25 on the occasion of the "Day of Africa".
 Present there on invitation were Choe Su Hon, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, and other officials concerned and diplomatic envoys and staff members of foreign embassies here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Staff members of African embassies here were on hand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers said that the formation of the Organization of African Unity (OAU) on May 25, 1963 marked an event of epoch-making significance in the struggle to finally abolish colonialism, racism and apartheid in Africa and achieve the total liberation and unity of Africa. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They expressed belief that the OAU would successfully fulfill its mission to build independent, peaceful and prosperous Africa in the future.

Reception Given on Chongryon Anniversary 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 26 (KCNA) -- A reception was given at the People's Palace of Culture Wednesday evening to celebrate the 50th anniversary of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon).
 Present there on invitation were members of delegations and visiting groups of Chongryon including a group for expressing thanks led by Nam Sung U, vice-chairman of the Central Standing Committee of Chongryon, and a delegation of Chongryon officials led by O Hyong Jin, director of the History Institute of Koreans in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also present were Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, Kim Jung Rin, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, Kim Yong Dae, chairman of the Central Committee of the Korean Social Democratic Party, Kim Wan Su, director of the Secretariat of the Central Committee of the Democratic Front for the Reunification of the Fatherland, leading officials of working people's organizations, officials concerned and those related to Chongryon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Yang Hyong Sop said in his speech that Chongryon has performed great exploits for the homeland and the nation under the wise leadership of President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il, recording a proud history shining with patriotism and loyalty during the last 50 years since its inauguration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The homeland and people will always remember the officials of Chongryon and the Koreans in Japan who have made a great contribution to the nation-wide cause of the prosperity of the homeland and national reunification, sharing destiny with the socialist homeland over the last 50 years under uplifted banner of Juche, he said, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il clearly indicated the way to be followed by the movement of Koreans in Japan and showed all love and care for the Chongryon officials and the Koreans in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Chongryon officials and the Koreans in Japan should as ever steadily develop Chongryon into an overseas compatriots' organization of Juche type remaining always boundlessly loyal to Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nam Sung U in his speech said Chongryon proud of being a model for the movement of compatriots overseas in the world and the worthy patriotic life of the Koreans in Japan could shine as Kim Il Sung formed Chongryon, a genuine overseas compatriots organization of Juche type, and led the movement of Koreans in Japan to victory. 
 He continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The immortal exploits performed by Kim Il Sung in the history of the Juche-oriented overseas compatriots movement are made to throw brighter rays in the new century by Kim Jong Il, the brilliant Songun commander of Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il met officials of Chongryon visiting the homeland and showed deep trust and loving care for them, though he found his days so full in leading the Songun revolution. He also sent a large amount of fund for the strengthening of Chongryon. We will always remember this great favor down through centuries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Chongryon officials and the Koreans in Japan will bring a decisive turn in the work of Chongryon and the movement of Koreans in Japan and make a more tangible contribution to national reunification and the prosperity of the homeland by powerfully rousing the patriotic zeal of the compatriot masses in step with the people of the homeland in their general march for the Songun revolution to glorify the 60th anniversaries of the Workers' Party of Korea and the liberation of the country as great festivals of victors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An art performance was given by artistes at the reception.

Anniversary of Kim Il Sung's Algeria Visit Observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 26 (KCNA) -- The brilliant exploits performed by President Kim Il Sung in external activities for the increase of the anti-imperialist independent forces of the world and the human cause of independence will be immortal, says Rodong Sinmun Thursday in a signed article dedicated to the 30th anniversary of his visit to Algeria.
 Through the historic visit, the President made an immortal contribution to expanding and developing the external relations and activities of the DPRK,
strengthening the non-aligned movement and achieving friendship and unity among the developing countries, the article says, and continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 While staying in Algeria, the President in his talks and speeches clarified the revolutionary stand and the external policy line of the DPRK and, on the basis of a scientific analysis of the features of the then international situation and trend of the development of the international relations, lucidly expounded the significance of strengthening friendship and unity and solidarity by Algeria and other developing countries and questions arising in its realization. He also elucidated all the matters of principle and ways for settling complicated international issues, strengthening the anti-imperialist independent forces including the non-aligned movement and accelerating the global cause of independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His Algeria visit went a long way toward strengthening friendship and unity among the developing countries and the anti-imperialist independent forces of the world including the non-aligned movement and promoting the human cause of independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With his Algeria visit as an occasion, friendship and unity and solidarity between the Korean people and the African peoples including the Algerian people and peoples of other developing countries grew in scope and the struggle of the progressive people of the world against the imperialists' policy of domination and moves of aggression and nterference and for the independent development of the countries and nations and the human cause of independence gathered force. Decades have passed since the President made the long journey to Algeria and a lot of changes have been noticed in the international arena. But the exploits he performed in his external activities will shine endlessly with the progress of history and they serve still today as a mighty driving power for friendship and unity of the anti-imperialist independent forces of the world and the cause of global independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the unshakable will of the Workers' Party and people of Korea to add shine to his immortal exploits in external activities generation after generation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people will as always strive to develop the friendly and cooperative relations with the African peoples including the Algerian people.

Polyazin for Protection of DNA Developed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 26 (KCNA) -- Teachers and researchers of the Hereditary Medicine Department of Pyongyang University of Medicine of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea have developed a new medicine "Polyazin" for protection of DNA.
 It is made with materials extracted from rare medicinal herbs growing in the northern mountainous areas of Korea, mixed with activator. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Prof. and Dr. Kim Yong Jin, who led the research team, told KCNA that the medicine not only prevents the bioactive material from being changed by heavy metals, harmful chemical matters and radioactive rays but also protects DNA by activating the medium around it.
 It is highly appreciated by special institutions as an ideal medicine for those working in the atomic energy sector and electromagnetic field and for the computer users. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The clinical tests show that it, with high alcoholysis, gives no side-effects. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It improves metabolism in liver, biliary tract, blood, immunity and psychoneurosis systems. It is also potent for the patients suffering from hypogonadism, chronic hepatitis, chronic pancreatitis and hypoacidity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also regulates physiological activity in human body and thus delights women who want to give birth to healthy and intelligent babies.

Kim Jong Il Gives Field Guidance to Construction Site of Wonsan Youth Power Station
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 26 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the National Defence Commission of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, gave field guidance to the construction site of the Wonsan Youth Power Station.
 He was greeted on the spot by senior officials of the province and the construction enterprise. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The province set the ambitious goal of constructing the power station with a huge capacity on its own efforts and has since pushed forward the project at a rapid tempo by focusing efforts on it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The construction of a huge dam in Komithan River rich in water resources and the appearance of a large man-made reservoir would make it possible to build several terraced power stations producing a lot of electricity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was briefed on the construction before the panoramic map of the station. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Then he went round the construction site to acquaint himself in detail with the progress of the project. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was greatly satisfied to see the nation's one more edifice of eternal value rising, noting its site was chosen in a good place and its designing was done well in line with the principle of profitability. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He highly appreciated the merits of the members of the youth shock brigade and other builders, greatly pleased to learn that they have done a great deal of work in a short span of time by waging a high-pitched drive with ardent patriotism. He extended warm appreciation to all the builders who have devoted themselves to the prosperity of the country with loyalty. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Many new edifices are now appearing in different parts of the country to be handed down to posterity along with the era of Songun thanks to the devoted efforts of our servicepersons and people single-mindedly united around the Party, he noted, adding this stirring reality clearly proves the inexhaustible strength and strong mental power of our army and people fully determined to accomplish the cause of building a great prosperous powerful nation with flying colors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saying that the Wonsan Youth Power Station is of great importance in realizing the electrification in Wonsan City, he set forth important tasks which would serve as guidelines in completing its construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Underscoring the need to build the power station to win the admiration of posterity because it is an edifice of eternal value to be handed down to the generations to come, he called for paying special attention to ensuring the best quality of the construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is very important for Kangwon Province to make an effective use of its rich hydro-power resources as it abounds in large and small rivers and streams and has a big rainfall, he said, underlining the need to thoroughly implement the WPK's policy of massively constructing minor power stations along with large ones. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed expectation and conviction that its builders would bring about a new turn in the construction by displaying popular heroism and matchless devotion and thus exalt their honor of being proud victors.
